snippet: Zdenek Hruby, the head of the Czech mountaineering federation, died while climbing Gasherbrum I, a 26,469-foot peak in the northern Pakistani Karakoram range, the federation said on its Web site.
lead_paragraph: Zdenek Hruby, the head of the Czech mountaineering federation, died while climbing Gasherbrum I, a 26,469-foot peak in the northern Pakistani Karakoram range, the federation said on its Web site.

headline.main: Czech Mountain Climber Dies in Pakistan
